                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1454-1">AMS, I, 95- 119 ; BHO, 1049- 51.
Suhadii', I, 42- 68.
Cureton, Documents, 41-62.
R. Duval, dans JA 8:14 (1889) , 40- 58.
BS, XI, 651-53 (J.-M. Sauget) .
Sauget , "Fragment" ' 225-28, propose !'identification de Sarbil a THUTHAEL (q.v.) et
a EUTAL (q.v.).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Sharbel and his sister Babai were martyrs of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>. Sharbel had been a pagan priest, but he converted to Christianity. He was martyred under Trajan. Sharbel and Babai were contemporary with the priest <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1162">Barsamya</persName>.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1454-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on Jan. 29, Sep. 5 (BHO).</desc>
                    </event>
